orangelight.title: i3569: add a sequence diagram of ILLiad request
Senior theses are not passing author information to aeon

comments.body: My original hunch was incorrect.  Aeon needs this info in the `ItemAuthor` field.  The `aeon_mapped_params` method will provide this, but we are bypassing it when we render a button that links directly to aeon.

What storage should we use in production and production-like environments? It looks like the suggested storage is for production is either Redis or MemcacheStore (not much explanation for this one), but from what I can see Redis is not yet configured for Orangelight. 

See https://github.com/MiniProfiler/rack-mini-profiler#storage

We discussed this existing ticket: https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/issues/2799

Our preferred approach would be to create a new Redis 6 box, and point Orangelight to it.
See also issue to add Redis to Orangelight in Ansible - https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/issues/3935
